<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Slack apps &amp; utilities</title>
    <meta name=viewport content="width=device-width">
    <meta name="description" content="A collection of useful Slack apps.">
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all' %>
    <script src="https://use.typekit.net/<%= ENV['TYPEKIT_ID'] %>.js" onload="try{Typekit.load({async:true});}catch(e){}" async=async></script>
    <% if ENV['GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID'].present? %>
      <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=<%= ENV['GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID'] %>"></script>
      <script>
        window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
        function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments)};
        gtag('js', new Date());

        gtag('config', '<%= ENV['GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID'] %>');
      </script>
    <% end %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <% flash.each do |name, msg| -%>
        <div class="flash <%= "flash--#{name}" %>">
          <p class="flash__message"><%= msg %></p>
        </div>
      <% end -%>

      <%= yield %>

      <footer class="footer">
        <p>
          None of your Slack teamâ€™s private information (such as names, channels, messages, etc.) is accessed or stored in any way.<br/>
          This app is not affiliated with Slack, Capital Bikeshare, Citibike, forecast.io, Frinkiac, or anyone else, really.<br/>
          The code is available on <a href="https://github.com/gesteves/slackbots">Github</a>, if you want to check it out.<br/>
          <a href="https://github.com/twitter/twemoji">Twemoji</a> icons by <a href="https://github.com/twitter">Twitter</a>, licensed under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">CC-BY</a>.<br/>
          Need help? Feel free to <a href="https://github.com/gesteves/slackbots/issues">open an issue</a>, but I cannot offer much in the way of support for these apps.<br/>
          Did you enjoy this? <a href="https://twitter.com/gesteves">Let me know</a>!
        </p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
